
#This below project is made for learning purpose to check the knowledged.

Create directory structure:

devops_project/
   ├── logs/
   ├── scripts/
   └── backup/

Create file inside logs:

app.log

Add 20 lines of random text to app.log.

Display only last 5 lines.

Count number of lines in file.

Copy app.log into backup folder.

Delete original file.


# Below are the project used commands

# Created directory structure: 

~$ mkdir -p devops_project/{log,scripts,backup}

# Create app.log file inside logs:

~$ cd devops_project/
~/devops_project$ cd log/
~/devops_project/log$ touch app.log

# Add 20 lines of random text to app.log. ( i used small sheckk script by forloop)

for i in {1..20}; do echo $(cat /dev/urandom | tr -dc 'a-zA-Z0-9' | head -c 20); done >> app.log

#Display only last 5 lines.

:~/devops_project/log$ tail -5f app.log
zBHbmloQkJqjKxxnO6f
AZ8cw2bkmu9NuYQ
n7IToslZ055JYYkW
vej91JfUB4EBaTx
KGK5fGHy0fsLAri

# Count number of lines in file.

~/devops_project/backup$ wc -l app.log
20 app.log


#Copy app.log into backup folder.

~/devops_project/log$ pwd
/home/binaya-p/devops_project/log
~/devops_project/log$ cp app.log ../backup
~/devops_project$ ls -l backup/
total 4
-rw-rw-r-- 1 binaya-p binaya-p 420 Feb 24 01:20 app.log

#Delete original file.

binaya-p@binaya-p-VMware-Virtual-Platform:~/devops_project/log$ rm -rv app.log
removed 'app.log'


